						<p>Tiers of the southern wall, Akhilāṇḍēśvara temple.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Year: 1[.]</hi></p>						

						<p>Damaged and incomplete. Seems to record an agreement by the <hi rend="italic">ūrār</hi> of E[śaya]ṉūr-nāḍu in Dāmar-kōṭṭam in respect of a grant of land made tax-free to provide five drummers and food offerings for <hi rend="italic">śrībali</hi> during the <hi rend="italic">paḷḷieḻuchchi</hi> service to the god.</p>						

